#lg E	kirugu


@(A.E.18 = 18-31) Trustworthy warrior, I will praise you! Lord @wDN{Lugal-era}, I will praise you! You are the great and august neck-stock of the gods, you are a great awesomeness resting heavily upon the Land, a heavy flood-wave covering the foreign land. Your river is a mighty river, the river which determines destinies, an august river where the sun rises, which nobody can bear to look upon. Great barge riding on the flood waters, Lord @wDN{Lugal-era}: when you set foot in the place where all mankind is gathered, the princes of the underworld bow down before you; in the abyss you emit a bright light to them. …… has been placed in your hands. Lord @wDN{Lugal-era}, your greatness extends to the outer limits of heaven.

