#lg G	kirugu


@(A.G.35 = 35-43) My king, let me tell of your greatness! Lord @wDN{Lugal-era}, I will praise your greatness! You are august, you alone are august! Mighty god surpassing all the gods, elevated king reaching up to the heavens, mighty god, trustworthy lord by himself, @wDN{River of the Ordeal}, heart of the gods, decision-making lord who hates evil, who like @wDN{Suen} loves justice.

@(A.G.44 = 44-61) They are the lords for whom @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil} have determined their destiny. When everything had been brought into existence in heaven and earth, their destiny greatly ……. @wDN{Enlil} granted ……. …… of the princes, my @wRN{Ibbi-@wDN{Suen}}! …… is great, a great wall which …… the foreign lands. Perfecting the great divine powers, he, the son of @wDN{Enlil}, …… the wicked like @wDN{Lugal-era}. In his august power @wDN{Mešlamta-ea} greatly, in his august power he greatly ……. When he opens his mouth ……, eradicating the foreign lands, …… he heaps up the enemies in piles. In his august power Lord @wDN{Lugal-era} greatly, in his august power he greatly ……, …… a favourable sign. They are kings ……. They are …… sparing ……  ((1 line fragmentary))   ((unknown no. of lines missing)) 


#lg H	kirugu


@(B.H.1 = 1-13) They are great warriors: their greatness is like the empty desert wastes. They are both the lords of the River, the @wDN{River of the Ordeal} which clears the just man. They weigh upon the evil man like a neck-stock. In @wSN{Kisiga}, their very anciently founded city, the trustworthy does not get caught, but the evil cannot pass through. They are a source of comfort to the hearts of @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil}, they are a source of relaxation ……. They are …… the great place ……. The place for which @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil} have determined its destiny ……, its divine powers are holy ……  ((2 lines fragmentary))   ((unknown no. of lines missing)) 


